  "bib_entries": {
    "17609886": {
      "title": "Generalized fusion potentials",
      "abstract": "Abstract Recently, Di Francesco and Zuber have characterized the RCFTs which have a description in terms of a fusion potential in one variable, and proposed a generalized potential to describe other theories. In this note we give a simple criterion to determine when such a generalized description is possible. We also determine which RCFTs can be described by a fusion potential in more than one variable, finding that in fact all RCFTs can be described in such a way, as conjectured by Gepner."
    }
  }
}